attribute.headline: Diamonds aren't forever at Kozminsky
attribute.text: It's a Melbourne institution frequented for more than a century by the city's wealthy establishment, by prime ministers, business leaders and visiting Hollywood movie stars. It's jewellery, silver antiques, objets d'art and other shining wares were bought to mark life's great moments: engagements, weddings, 21st birthday parties and other special events. attribute.headline: Bunnings to test Britain's DIY market
attribute.text: Exclusive | Bunnings faces it first big test in Britain when the do-it-yourself chain opens in Hertfordshire this week. The store opens in a market where cheap tradespeople from eastern Europe have created a "do it for me" culture and there is a lack of interest among young people in tackling home improvement projects.
